<br>
I do have to say that I've beta'd a number of games, and this team is, by far, one of the most involved and exciting to work with ... At least in my honest opinion.  They listened to what we had to say, kept us aware of what was going on, hell, told us in advance when account and character wipes were going to occur.  <br>
<br>
They held weekly events that used or advanced the storyline ... which I thought was a very swifty thing during a beta.  By far and away a much MUCH better experience than when I beta'd Shadowbane (ick)<br>
<br>
The game is absolutely beautiful, graphics-wise,  and the interface fairly intuitive.  Crafting is a bit tedious ... but uses a system that makes sense.<br>
<br>
Generally, when I beta or alpha/beta a game, I've a tendency to get so throroughly burned out on it that I never get around to buying the final copy.  This game I liked well enough to take a 2-3 week respite from testing so that I'd have even more fun with final.<br>
<br>
If that makes any sense <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
